'''阿曼達·S·C·戈爾曼'''<ref name="Walsh2018" />（{{lang-en|Amanda S. C. Gorman}}，{{bd|1998年|3月7日}}），美國[[詩人|詩人]]與[[社會活動家|社會活動家]]，首位{{link-en|國家青年桂冠詩人|National Youth Poet Laureate}}，其詩作題材主要集中在{{link-en|壓迫|oppression}}、[[女權主義|女權主義]]、[[美國種族及民族|美國種族問題]]、[[社會排斥|社會排斥]]與[[非裔|非裔族群]]上。她在2015年以17歲之齡出版詩集《為食不果腹者》（''The One for Whom Food Is Not Enough''）。2021年，戈爾曼在[[2021年美國總統就職典禮|2021年美國總統就職典禮]]上朗讀其詩作《{{link-en|我們攀登的山丘|The Hill We Climb}}》，她在典禮上朗誦的詩作贏得國際讚譽，不久之後，其詩集成為暢銷書，還獲得一份專業{{link-en|管理合同|Management contract}}。同年2月，戈曼獲選為《[[時代雜誌|時代]]》百大次世代領導人「奇才」之一，其簡介由演員[[林-曼努爾·米蘭達|林-曼努爾·米蘭達]]撰寫<ref name="2021 TIME100 Next">{{Cite web|title=2021 TIME100 Next: Amanda Gorman|url=https://time.com/collection/time100-next-2021/5937743/amanda-gorman/|access-date=2021-02-17|first=Lin-Manuel|last=Miranda|date=2021-02-17|website=Time}}</ref>。

== 早年生活和教育 ==
戈爾曼在1998年3月7日出生於美國[[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]][[洛杉磯|洛杉磯]]<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Coke|first=Hope|date=2021-01-21|title=Meet Amanda Gorman: The gifted young poet who shot to fame after her starring role in Biden's inauguration|work=Tatler|url=https://www.tatler.com/article/who-is-amanda-gorman-biden-inauguration-poet|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130194635/https://www.tatler.com/article/who-is-amanda-gorman-biden-inauguration-poet|archive-date=2021-01-30}}</ref>，由其任職英語教師的單身母親瓊恩（Joan）獨力扶養長大<ref>{{Cite web|title=6th Grade Humanities – Dr. Joan Wicks – Alliance Jack H. Skirball Middle School|url=https://www.skirballmiddle.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=284106&type=u&pREC_ID=340881|access-date=2021-01-25|website=www.skirballmiddle.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Ballard|first=Elise|date=2021-01-27|title=Amanda Gorman Was Mentored by a "Positive Community of Women Writers" Before Her Inaugural Moment|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amanda-gorman-was-mentored-by-a-positive-community-of-women-writers-before-her-inaugural-moment|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128161016/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amanda-gorman-was-mentored-by-a-positive-community-of-women-writers-before-her-inaugural-moment|archive-date=2021-01-28}}</ref>，並有兩個兄弟姊妹<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|last=Hassan|first=Adeel|date=2018-02-28|title=A Young Poet's Inspiration|language=en-US|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/28/us/a-young-poets-inspiration.html|access-date=2018-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180430120116/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/28/us/a-young-poets-inspiration.html|archive-date=2018-02-28|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2017/9/18/youth-poet/|title=Harvard Sophomore Chosen as First Youth Poet Laureate {{!}} News {{!}} The Harvard Crimson|first=Caroline S.|last=Engelmayer|date=2017-09-18|website=www.thecrimson.com|language=en |access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lataco.com/meet-amanda-gorman-the-l-a-native-who-is-the-first-national-youth-poet-laureate/|title=Meet Amanda Gorman, the L.A. Native Who Is the First National Youth Poet Laureate |author=Astrid|date=2018-03-22|work=L.A. TACO |access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://archives.nbclearn.com/portal/site/k-12/flatview?cuecard=114508|title=Meet the First Youth Poet Laureate|website=NBC Learn |access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>，其中加布麗埃勒（Gabrielle）為其攣生姐妹，長大後成為一位社會活動家<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/rise-up-as-one-video-featuring-poet-amanda-gorman-filmmaker-gabrielle-gorman-shows-how-powerful-resistance-can-be-when-its-intersectional-exclusive-7945545|title=These Twin Sisters Have A Powerful Message About Making Sure Your Resistance Includes All Women|last=Rodriguez-Cayro|first=Kyli|magazine=Bustle|date=2018-01-18|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en}}</ref>與電影製片人<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Luders-Manuel |first1=Shannon |title=Meet Gabrielle Gorman: Filmmaker and YoungArts Winner |url=https://www.essence.com/lifestyle/meet-gabrielle-gorman-filmmaker-and-youngarts-winner/ |access-date=2021-01-21 |magazine=Essence |date=2016-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Larsen |first1=Peter |title=Los Angeles native Amanda Gorman will be youngest poet to read at presidential inauguration |url=https://www.ocregister.com/2021/01/15/los-angeles-native-amanda-gorman-will-be-youngest-poet-to-read-at-presidential-inauguration/ |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The Orange County Register |date=2021-01-20}}</ref>。戈曼表示自己在缺乏電視信號的環境下長大<ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/americas-first-youth-poet-laureate-amanda-gorman-on-the-power-of-young-women|title=America's First Youth Poet Laureate Amanda Gorman on the Power of Young Women|last=Hawkins|first=Khaliha|magazine=Glamour |date=2018-06-04|access-date=2018-06-29|language=en}}</ref>，並形容年少時的她是一位「奇怪的小孩」，在母親的鼓勵下喜愛閱讀和寫作<ref name=":0" />。

戈爾曼患有{{link-en|中樞聽覺處理障礙|Auditory processing disorder}}，[[聽覺過敏|對聲音非常敏感]]<ref name=":0" />，也因此在兒時有著[[發音問題|發音上的問題]]，她在此期間曾接受過[[言語治療|言語治療]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/amanda-gorman/poetrys-relevance-to-yout_b_6000384.html|title=How Poetry Gave Me a Voice|last=Gorman|first=Amanda|date=2014-11-21|website=[[Huffington_Post|Huffington Post]]|language=en-US |access-date=2018-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Breslow |first1=Jason |title='History Has Its Eyes On Us.' Poet Amanda Gorman Seeks Right Words For Inauguration |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/biden-transition-updates/2021/01/19/958077401/history-has-its-eyes-on-us-poet-amanda-gorman-seeks-right-words-for-inauguration |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=Morning Edition|publisher=[[NPR|NPR]] |date=2021-01-19}}</ref>。《[[哈佛克里姆森報|哈佛克里姆森報]]》的伊莉妲·科查里安（Elida Kocharian）在2018年寫道：「戈爾曼並不認為自己的言語障礙是短板，而是將其視為天賦或力量」<ref name="Kocharian">{{cite news |last1=Kocharian |first1=Elida |title=American Lyricist |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2018/2/1/amanda-gorman-scrutling/ |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The Harvard Crimson |date=2018-02-01}}</ref>。戈爾曼在同年接受《[[哈佛校報|哈佛校報]]》的訪問時稱：「我一直把它（言語障礙）視作一種優勢，自從有了聽覺和語言上的障礙後，我變得非常擅長閱讀和寫作。當我在童年時意識到這回事時，我向媽媽唸誦了[[瑪麗安娜·威廉森|瑪麗安娜·威廉森]]的名句：『我們最深的恐懼不是信心不足，而是我們強大到無可估量』」<ref name="Walsh2018">{{cite news |last1=Walsh |first1=Colleen |title=The poetic perspective |url=https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2018/10/youth-poet-laureate-amanda-gorman-delivers-poem-at-harvard-presidents-inauguration/ |access-date=2021-01-22 |work=[[哈佛校報|The Harvard Gazette]]|date=2018-10-04}}</ref>。2021年，戈爾曼登上《[[CBS今晨|CBS今晨]]》時向主播之一的{{link-en|安東尼·曼森|Anthony Mason (journalist)}}表示會用歌唱的方式舒緩自己的病情：「我最喜歡唱的歌是《[[漢密爾頓_(音樂劇)|漢密爾頓]]》的〈[[阿龍·伯爾|阿龍·伯爾]]，先生〉（Aaron Burr, Sir,），原因是整首歌都充滿著R音，而我心想，如果我能跟上{{link-en|小萊斯利·奧多姆|Leslie Odom Jr.|萊斯利}}的節奏的話，那我就能說出詩中的R音了」<ref name="CBSNews2021">{{cite news |title=Amanda Gorman makes history as youngest known inaugural poet |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/amanda-gorman-inaugural-poet-the-hill-we-climb/ |access-date=2021-02-01 |work=CBS News |date=2021-01-21}}</ref>。

戈爾曼的[[K–12|K–12]]時段皆就讀於加州[[聖塔莫尼卡|聖塔莫尼卡]]的私立新路學校（New Roads School）<ref>{{cite web |title=16 Alumna and US Youth Poet Laureate Presents Poem at Library of Congress |url=https://www.newroads.org/news-story?pk=948670 |website=Newroads.org|date=2017-09-14}}</ref>，她在中學時獲得{{link-en|米爾肯家庭基金會|Milken Family Foundation}}的大學獎學金<ref>{{Cite news|date=2016-07-14|title=Santa Monica students win Milken scholarships|language=en-US|newspaper=Santa Monica Daily Press|url=https://www.smdp.com/santa-monica-students-win-milken-scholarships/156246 |first=Jeff|last=Goodman|access-date=2016-07-14}}</ref>。畢業後，戈爾曼前往[[哈佛大學|哈佛大學]]修讀[[社會學|社會學]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Flood|first=Alison|date=2021-01-19|title=Amanda Gorman will be youngest poet to recite at a presidential inauguration|url=http://www.theguardian.com/books/2021/jan/19/amanda-gorman-youngest-poet-to-recite-at-a-presidential-inauguration-joe-biden|archive-url=|archive-date= |access-date=2021-01-19|website=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|language=en}}</ref>，期間曾在2019年到西班牙的[[馬德里|馬德里]]留學一個學期<ref name=Observer.com>{{cite web|url=https://observer.com/2019/04/amanda-gorman-youth-poet-laureate-future-projects-women-in-the-world-summit/|title=The First Youth Poet Laureate, Amanda Gorman Wants You to Know Her Work Goes Beyond Words|last=Radin|first=Sara|website=Observer.com|date=2019-04-09|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iesabroad.org/news/ies-abroad-madrid-alum-amanda-gorman-shares-her-study-abroad-story#sthash.p2UBfdPB.z7UUGb64.dpbs|title=IES Abroad Madrid Alum Amanda Gorman Shares Her Study Abroad Story|website=IES Abroad|date=2021-01-22|access-date=2021-03-16}}</ref>，後在2020年以{{link-en|ΦΒΚ會|Phi Beta Kappa}}會員身份學成<ref>{{cite web |title=Phi Beta Kappa Member Amanda Gorman |url=https://www.pbk.org/News/Amanda-Gorman-reads-her-poem-The-Hill-We-Climb-a |website=The Phi Beta Kappa Society |access-date=2021-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Fernanda Baron and Amanda Gorman Elected to Senior PBK May 2020 |url=https://sociology.fas.harvard.edu/news/fernanda-baron-and-amanda-gorman-elected-senior-pbk |website=Department of Sociology |publisher=Harvard University |access-date=2021-01-31 |date=2021-01-21}}</ref>，並獲得優等[[拉丁文學位榮譽|拉丁文學位榮譽]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theamandagorman.com|title=Wordsmith. Change-maker|website=Amanda Gorman|access-date=2021-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/amanda-gorman|title=Amanda Gorman|website=Poetry Foundation|access-date=2021-01-21}}</ref>。

== 詩人生涯 ==
=== 2014–15 ===
戈爾曼的詩作題材主要集中在{{link-en|壓迫|oppression}}、[[女權主義|女權主義]]、[[美國種族及民族|美國種族問題]]、[[社會排斥|社會排斥]]與[[非裔|非裔族群]]<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|date=2018-02-28|title=A Coda to Black History Month|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/28/us/a-coda-to-black-history-month.html|first=Adeel|last= Hassan|access-date=2018-04-30|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mashable.com/2017/09/17/amanda-gorman-us-youth-poet-laureate-social-good/#.oPOIRaENiqO|title=Watch the first-ever U.S. youth poet laureate perform a stunning poem about social change|last=Petronzio|first=Matt|website=[[Mashable|Mashable]] |date=2017-09-17|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en}}</ref>。她表示自己在2013年看到[[諾貝爾和平獎|諾貝爾和平獎]]得主[[马拉拉·优素福扎伊|马拉拉·优素福扎伊]]的演講後受到啟發，立志成為[[聯合國|聯合國]]的青年大使<ref>{{Cite news|date=2017-11-03|title=How Amanda Gorman Became the Nation's First Youth Poet Laureate|first=Alex|last= Hawgood|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/03/style/amanda-gorman-first-youth-poet-laureate.html |access-date=2018-04-30|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>。戈曼在隔年獲選為洛杉磯首位青年[[桂冠詩人|桂冠詩人]]<ref>{{Cite news|date=2015-04-24|title=Mentoring the Next Generation of L.A. Letters|language=en|work=KCET|url=https://www.kcet.org/history-society/mentoring-the-next-generation-of-la-letters |first=Mike|last= Sonksen|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>。她在同年據報正為自己在過去兩年內寫的小說編修初稿，當時其年僅16歲<ref name=":5">{{Cite news|last=Thomson|first=Hilary|date=2014-05-27|title=Writes of Passage|work=Trek|publisher=[[University_of_British_Columbia|University of British Columbia]]|url=https://trekmagazine.alumni.ubc.ca/2014/may-2014/features/writes-of-passage/|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603203444/https://trekmagazine.alumni.ubc.ca/2014/may-2014/features/writes-of-passage/|archive-date=2020-06-03}}</ref>。2015年，戈爾曼的第一部詩集《為食不果腹者》（''The One for Whom Food Is Not Enough''）<ref>{{Cite news|title=A young poet for whom words are not enough|first=Sophia|last= Eppolito|newspaper=[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/2017/09/21/young-poet-for-whom-words-are-not-enough/o54NK48fpuThupPFTzahII/story.html |date=2017-09-21|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>。

=== 2016–20 ===
[[File:Amanda_Gorman_with_Tracy_K_Smith_-_2017_crop.jpeg|225px]]館長[[卡拉·海登|卡拉·海登]]（左）、桂冠詩人{{link-en|崔西·K·史密斯|Tracy K. Smith}}（中）與戈爾曼]]
戈爾曼在2016年以18歲之齡創立非營利組織「一支筆一頁紙」（One Pen One Page），鼓勵青年寫作和發揮領導力<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gilpin |first1=Caroline Crosson |title=Do You Read or Write Poetry? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/07/learning/do-you-read-or-write-poetry.html |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The New York Times |date=2017-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/us/gender-letter-all-the-poetry-thats-fit-to-print.html|title=Gender Letter: All the Poetry That's Fit to Print|date=2018-04-26|work=The New York Times |access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>。隔年4月，她從五位候選人中突圍而出<ref>{{Cite news|last=Charles|first=Ron|date=2017-09-14|title=New U.S. Poet Laureate Tracy K. Smith reports for duty|language=en-US|newspaper=The Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/new-us-poet-laureate-tracy-k-smith-reports-for-duty/2017/09/14/9f14b014-9950-11e7-87fc-c3f7ee4035c9_story.html|access-date=2018-04-30|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>，成為首位{{link-en|國家青年桂冠詩人|National Youth Poet Laureate}}<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":1" />，之後獲[[耐克|耐克]]邀請為黑人運動員寫詩打氣<ref>{{cite web|last=Italie|first=Hillel|title=Meet Amanda Gorman, the 22-year-old poet chosen to read at the inauguration of Joe Biden|url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/nation-world/ct-inauguration-ceremony-poet-youngest-in-memory-20210115-d5pu65eygra6lhagutnrevvpuu-story.html |date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-17|website=baltimoresun.com}}</ref>，還與[[維京出版社|維京出版社]]合作，發行兩本兒童向畫集<ref>{{Cite web|title=Poet Amanda Gorman, 22, Will Read at Biden's Inauguration|first=Hillel|last=Italie|url=https://time.com/5930015/poet-amanda-gorman-biden-inauguration/ |date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-17|website=Time}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Poet and former Youth Laureate Amanda Gorman has book deal|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2019/07/11/poet-and-former-youth-laureate-amanda-gorman-has-book-deal/kZ1VkcCmLLLCvBt0UwzGqK/story.html |date=2019-07-11|access-date=2021-01-17|newspaper=The Boston Globe|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|language=en-US}}</ref>。

2017年9月18日，戈爾曼成為為[[美國國家圖書館|美國國家圖書館]]的文學季活動開幕的青年詩人，她在圖書館內朗讀其為此活動和慶祝{{link-en|崔西·K·史密斯|Tracy K. Smith}}成為[[桂冠詩人|桂冠詩人]]所作的詩《在這地方：一首美國抒情詩》（''In This Place: An American Lyric''）<ref name="Kocharian" />，全程由[[音樂電視網|音樂電視網]]直播<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|title=Harvard's Amanda Gorman first youth poet to open Library of Congress literary season|newspaper=The Boston Globe|first=Sophia|last= Eppolito|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/2017/09/18/harvard-amanda-gorman-first-youth-poet-open-library-congress-literary-season/IXhK2LBt7NHYSkTXpDSqcL/story.html|date=2017-09-18|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>。[[摩根圖書館與博物館|摩根圖書館與博物館]]隨後購得《在這地方：一首美國抒情詩》，並在2018年在[[伊麗莎白·畢曉普|伊麗莎白·畢曉普]]的作品附近展出<ref name=":4" />。此外，戈爾曼還在2017年獲得媒體公司「{{link-en|OZY|OZY (media company)}}」每年頒發的1萬美元獎學金，該獎學金志在給予「追求卓越理念和革新想法」的10位大學生<ref>{{Cite web|date=2017-12-01|title=How a Young Poet Is Nurturing Empathy ... With Virtual Reality|first=Nick|last=Fouriezos|url=https://www.ozy.com/true-and-stories/how-a-young-poet-is-nurturing-empathy-with-virtual-reality/77355/|access-date=2021-01-21|website=OZY}}</ref>。她更表示希望在2036年角逐美國總統職位<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.essence.com/culture/first-youth-poet-laureate-Amanda-Gorman-president|title=America's First Youth Poet Laureate Also Wants to Run For President In 2036!|magazine=Essence |first=Paula|last=Rego|date=2017-11-04| access-date=2018-04-30|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/americas-20-year-old-youth-poet-laureate-wont-let-small-minded-prejudice-stop-215752247.html|title=America's 20-year-old youth poet laureate won't let 'small-minded prejudice' stop her |first=Elena|last=Sheppard|website=Yahoo!|date=2018-05-29|access-date=2018-06-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Julia|last=Barajas|date=2021-01-17|title=How a 22-year-old L.A. native became Biden's inauguration poet|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/books/story/2021-01-17/amanda-gorman-biden-inauguration-poet|access-date=2021-01-22|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|language=en-US}}</ref>，隨後幾年亦不斷提起這願望<ref name="BGlobe2021-01-20-01a">{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/2021/01/20/lifestyle/we-will-never-again-sow-division-harvard-graduate-amanda-gorman-delivers-inaugural-poem/|title=Amid presidents and pop stars, poet Amanda Gorman grabs the spotlight at inauguration|newspaper=The Boston Globe|first=Hanna|last= Krueger |author2=Diti Kohli |date=2021-01-10|access-date=2021-01-11|quote=She plans on taking the oath of office herself. 'I always say the really, really long-term goal, meaning 2036, is to become president,' Gorman said in a 2017 interview with the Globe after being named the first National Youth Poet Laureate. She has repeated the hope in interviews ever since.}}</ref>。被選為《{{link-en|魅力 (雜誌)|Glamour (magazine)|魅力}}》10大「2018年度大學女性」時，戈爾曼表示：「以年輕黑人女性的身份啟發人們是我想在政治範疇上繼續做下去的事，我想把它化做現實和行動，而不僅僅流於文筆之上」<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.glamour.com/gallery/meet-glamours-2018-college-women-of-the-year|title=Meet ''Glamour''{{'}}s 2018 College Women of the Year|first=Jessica|last=Militare|magazine=Glamour|date=2018-06-04}}</ref>。

戈爾曼在2019年獲列入《{{link-en|根源雜誌|The Root}}》的25大「青年未來人」內，成為「25位在社會正義與行動主義、藝術與文化、企業與公司創新、科學與技術和綠色創新領域表現卓越的優秀傑出[[非裔美國人|非裔美國人]]」之一<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theroot.com/2019-young-futurists-for-these-25-game-changers-the-f-1833243246|title=2019 Young Futurists: For These 25 Game Changers, the Future Is Now|website=The Root|date=2019-03-27|access-date=2021-01-26}}</ref>。2020年5月，她在[[約翰·卡拉辛斯基|約翰·卡拉辛斯基]]的[[網路劇|網路劇]]《{{link-en|一些好消息|Some Good News}}》上與[[奧花·雲費|奧花·雲費]]進行[[視訊電話|視像會談]]，並為受[[2019冠狀病毒病美國疫情|美國COVID-19疫情]]而無法回校的學生發表畢業典禮演講<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/amanda-gorman-poet-inauguration-joe-biden-1234888023/|title=Who Is 22-Year-Old Inaugural Poet Amanda Gorman?|first=Mónica|last=Marie Zorrilla|magazine=[[Variety_(magazine)|Variety]]|date=2021-01-20|access-date=2021-01-21}}</ref>。同年，戈爾曼發表關於[[氣候變化|氣候變化]]的詩作《地出》（''Earthrise''）<ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-10-25|title='Earthrise' poem dares us to dream a different reality|first=Ted|last=Countdown|url=https://racetozero.unfccc.int/earthrise-poem-dares-us-to-dream-a-different-reality/|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Race to Zero|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Holthaus|first=Eric|title=Amanda Gorman, the climate poet for our time|url=https://thephoenix.substack.com/p/amanda-gorman-the-climate-poet-for|date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-21|website=thephoenix.substack.com}}</ref>。

=== 2021年與美國總統就職典禮 ===
[[File:210120-D-WD757-2714_(50861221216).jpg|225px]]準備朗誦《{{link-en|我們攀登的山丘|The Hill We Climb}}》的戈爾曼]]
受候任[[美國第一夫人|第一夫人]][[吉兒·拜登|吉兒·拜登]]的邀請<ref>{{cite news |first1=Alexandra |last1=Alter |title=Amanda Gorman, a 22-year-old poet, asks 'Where can we find light?' in Inauguration Day recitation. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/20/us/who-is-amanda-gorman-poet-inauguration.html |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The New York Times |date=2021-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Amanda Gorman, 22, Will Be the Youngest Poet to Read at an Inauguration Day Ceremony|url=https://people.com/politics/amanda-gorman-will-be-the-youngest-poet-to-read-at-the-inauguration-day/ |date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-17|first= Sean|last= Neumann|website=[[人物_(雜誌)|PEOPLE.com]]|language=EN}}</ref>，戈爾曼在2021年1月20日的[[2021年美國總統就職典禮|美國總統就職典禮]]上誦讀其詩作《{{link-en|我們攀登的山丘|The Hill We Climb}}》，是美國史上最年輕的總統就職典禮詩人<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bideninaugural.org/presidential-inaugural-committee-announces-participants-in-the-59th-inaugural-ceremonies/|title=Presidential Inaugural Committee Announces Participants in the 59th Inaugural Ceremonies|date=2021-01-14|website=bideninaugural.org}}</ref><ref name=Gabbatt>{{cite news |last1=Gabbatt |first1=Adam |title='An inspiration to us all': Amanda Gorman's inaugural poem stirs hope and awe |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/20/amanda-gorman-poem-biden-inauguration |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The Guardian |date=2021-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Shalal |first1=Andrea |title=Poet Amanda Gorman, 22, captures 'bruised, but whole' U.S. at Biden, Harris inauguration |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-biden-inauguration-poetry/poet-amanda-gorman-22-captures-bruised-but-whole-u-s-at-biden-harris-inauguration-idUSKBN29P2KA |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=Reuters |date=2021-01-20}}</ref>。稍早前的1月6日，她為了回應[[2021年美國國會大廈遭衝擊事件|衝擊國會大廈事件]]而修改部分詩詞<ref>{{Cite news|last=Inskeep|first=Steve|date=2021-01-19|title='History Has Its Eyes On Us.' Poet Amanda Gorman Seeks Right Words For Inauguration
|publisher=NPR|url=https://www.npr.org/transcripts/958077401|access-date=2021-01-19}} Transcript of interview.</ref><ref name="CBSNews2021" />。在就職典禮的前一周，戈爾曼接受《[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]》評論家羅恩·查爾斯（Ron Charles）的訪問時表示：「我希望我的詩（《我們攀登的山丘》）在未來成為團結美國的契機 […] 憑藉自己的言詞，我便能為我國開創新的篇章和時代」<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wang |first1=Amy B |last2=Merry |first2=Stephanie |title=Amanda Gorman reads poem 'The Hill We Climb' at Biden inauguration |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/2021/01/20/amanda-gorman-poet-laureate-inauguration/ |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The Washington Post |date=2021-01-20}}</ref>。在登台誦詩前，她向《CBS今晨》的其中一位主播安東尼·曼森說：「其中一個我會在朗誦前做的事，是對自己念一句咒語：『我是黑人作家的女兒。我們是破牢而出並改變世界的自由鬥士的後代』。這就是我為需要去完成的任務做好準備的方式」<ref name="CBSNews2021" />。就職典禮後，前任[[美國國務卿|美國國務卿]]與第一夫人[[希拉蕊·克林頓|希拉蕊·克林頓]]發推文表示支持戈爾曼於2036年競逐總統職位<ref name="BBC2021-01-20-01a">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-55738564|title=Amanda Gorman: Inauguration poet calls for 'unity and togetherness'|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|author=|date=2021-01-10|access-date=2021-01-11|quote=Hillary Clinton tweeted that Gorman had promised to run for president in 2036 and added: 'I for one can't wait.'}}</ref>。

在總統就職典禮上頌詩後不久，戈爾曼即將於2021年9月出版<ref name=Kenya/>的兩本作品《我們攀登的山丘》（詩集）和《變革在歌唱：兒童的國歌》（''Change Sings: A Children's Anthem''）登上[[亞馬遜公司|亞馬遜]]暢銷書榜單的首位<ref name=Kenya>{{cite news |last1=Evelyn |first1=Kenya |title=Amanda Gorman books top bestselling lists after soul-stirring inaugural poem |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2021/jan/21/amanda-gorman-star-rises-inaugural-poem |access-date=2021-01-21 |work=The Guardian |date=2021-01-21}}</ref>。由[[奧花·雲費|奧花·雲費]]撰寫序言的實體書版《我們攀登的山丘》則在同年3月16日發行，而她即將出版的三本書的初版都將印刷一百萬冊<ref>{{cite news |last1=Italie |first1=Hillel |title=Interest continues to grow in inaugural poet Amanda Gorman |url=https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-entertainment-poetry-oprah-winfrey-9c51ba6bff092b2c83412e982ff82e13 |access-date=2021-01-28 |work=Associated Press |date=2021-01-28}}</ref>。2021年2月，2020年[[布克國際獎|布克國際獎]]得主[[瑪麗克·盧卡斯·莉涅維德|瑪麗克·盧卡斯·莉涅維德]]在被抨擊不應由白人擔任翻譯後，決定辭謝將戈爾曼的詩作翻譯為[[荷蘭語|荷蘭語]]的邀約<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/article/rijneveld-gorman-translation-uproar-e5b9d81cb2e50e7ce3906d1f850ed261|title=Dutch poet declines assignment to translate Gorman’s works|agency=Associated Press|date=2021-02-26|access-date=2021-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/amanda-gorman-poem-translation-dutch-b1808315.html|title=Dutch writer Marieke Lucas Rijneveld steps down from assignment to translate Amanda Gorman’s work|first=Clémence|last= Michallon|newspaper=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|date=2021-02-26}}</ref>。

戈爾曼在總統就職典禮上穿著的[[普拉達|普拉達]]服飾亦備受注目，模特事務所{{link-en|IMG Models|IMG Models}}和其母公司[[威廉·莫里斯奮進|威廉·莫里斯奮進]]不久之後便跟她簽訂了時尚美容方面的代理合約<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/books/story/2021-01-26/amanda-gorman-img-models-presidency|title=Amanda Gorman signs with IMG Models, but we all know it's the presidency she's after|work=Los Angeles Times|date=2021-01-26|last=Saad|first=Nardine}}</ref>。而Writers House和the Gang, Tyre, Ramer, Brown and Passman則分別是戈爾曼在文學和法律事務上的代理人<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gardner|first=Chris|date=2021-01-25|title=Inaugural Poet Amanda Gorman Signs With IMG Models|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/inaugural-poet-amanda-gorman-signs-with-img-models|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130091154/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/inaugural-poet-amanda-gorman-signs-with-img-models|archive-date=2021-01-30}}</ref>。她隨後受[[國家美式足球聯盟|國家美式足球聯盟]]所託撰寫一首全新的詩作，在2021年2月7日[[第五十五届超级碗|第五十五届超级碗]]賽前儀式上播出的介紹三位[[擲硬幣|擲硬幣]]的榮譽隊長的影片中朗讀<ref>{{Cite news|last=Garrand|first=Danielle|date=2021-01-28|title=Inaugural poet Amanda Gorman to perform original piece at Super Bowl|work=[[CBS_News|CBS News]]|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/amanda-gorman-super-bowl-performance-poem/|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129110004/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/amanda-gorman-super-bowl-performance-poem/|archive-date=2021-01-29}}</ref>。《[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]》報導指三位榮譽隊長美國海軍老兵詹姆斯·馬丁（James Martin）；老師特里梅恩·戴維斯（Trimaine Davis）；以及[[加護病房|ICU]]護士長蘇茜·多納（Suzie Dorner）都是必不可少的工作者<ref>{{cite news |last1=McGuire |first1=Nneka |title=Amanda Gorman clearly has talent. But there's more to her meteoric rise. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/amanda-gorman-super-bowl/2021/02/07/1a226478-699f-11eb-9ead-673168d5b874_story.html |access-date=2021-02-08 |work=The Washington Post |date=2021-02-08}}</ref>。在超級碗誦讀其新詩作《隊長們的合唱》（''Chorus of the Captains''）前，戈爾曼接受《[[滾石雜誌|滾石雜誌]]》訪問時表示：「超級碗上出現詩歌對藝術和我國而言都是一大壯舉，意味著即使我們感到孤單，我們還是會富有想像力地對人際關係進行思考<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/super-bowl-2021-amanda-gorman-poem-1124929/|title=Super Bowl 2021: Poet Amanda Gorman Honors NFL’s Three 'Honorary Captains'|magazine=[[Rolling_Stone|Rolling Stone]]|date=2021-02-07|access-date=2021-02-28}}</ref>」。

戈曼隨後登上《[[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]]》2021年2月號的封面<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Story Behind TIME's Amanda Gorman Cover|url=https://time.com/5935798/amanda-gorman-cover/|first=Sanya|last=Mansoor|date=2021-02-03|access-date=2021-02-16|website=Time}}</ref>。同年3月，她在被一位自己家附近的保安[[種族歸納|種族歸納]]後發推文稱：「他沒有抱歉就離開了。這就是黑人女孩要面對的現實：即使你有一天被視為榜樣，但到了另一天，你便是他們的眼中釘」<ref name="AP March 2021">{{cite news |title=Amanda Gorman says she was racially profiled near her home |url=https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-race-and-ethnicity-amanda-gorman-d986f597a840ff14fec7b37312a35a34 |access-date=2021-03-07 |work=Associated Press |date=2021-03-05}}</ref>。之後其再補充道：「就某程度而言，他是沒錯的。我是個威脅：對不公義、不平等和不知情的威脅。任何說真話並懷抱著希望向前走的人，對權力來說都是顯而易見且具毀滅性的危險，一種光榮的威脅」<ref name="AP March 2021"/>。

== 影響 ==
戈爾曼形容自己的早期創作時表示其風格很像《[[绿山墙的安妮|绿山墙的安妮]]》，直至在中學接觸到[[托妮·莫里森|托妮·莫里森]]的作品後才「那（莫里森的作品）故事實際上是可以發生在我，或是類似的人身上的」。《[[紐約觀察家報|紐約觀察家報]]》在2019年寫道：「在高中時，她（戈爾曼）閱讀了其他黑人女性的詩歌，例如[[奧德雷·洛德|奧德雷·洛德]]和{{link-en|菲莉絲·惠特利|Phillis Wheatley}}，並開始寫詩評論諸如[[交叉性|交叉性]][[女權主義|女權主義]]和種族等社會正義問題<ref name=Observer.com />」。談到時尚與詩歌之間的聯繫時，戈爾曼表示應循多門學科的角度表達自我。《[[時尚_(Vogue)|時尚]]》在2019年指她受到[[马娅·安杰卢|马娅·安杰卢]]、[[薩塞克斯公爵夫人梅根|薩塞克斯公爵夫人梅根]]和[[米歇爾·奧巴馬|米歇爾·奧巴馬]]等偶像的啟發，她對此表示：「時尚為語言帶來獨一無二的視覺美學，當我在舞台上朗誦時，我不僅會考慮該穿著什麼衣服，還會思考到底我的『[[黑豹_(電影)|瓦干達萬歲]]』T恤和黃色短裙會怎樣訴說我詩人的身份」<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/amanda-gorman-national-poet-laureate-milan-fashion-week-diary|title=Meet the Rising Poet Who Stole the Show at Milan Fashion Week|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|magazine=Vogue|date=2019-02-27|access-date=2021-03-16}}</ref>。

== 個人生活 ==
戈曼是一位天主教徒<ref>{{Cite web|last=Jones|first=Kevin|title=Amanda Gorman, inaugural poet for Biden, has history of abortion advocacy|url=https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/amanda-gorman-inaugural-poet-for-biden-has-history-of-abortion-advocacy|date= 2021-01-27|access-date=2021-01-31|website=Catholic News Agency|language=en}}</ref>，也是洛杉磯[[聖布麗姬|聖布麗姬]]天主教堂（St. Brigid Catholic Church）的成員<ref>{{cite news |last1=Molina |first1=Alejandra |title=At poet Amanda Gorman's Black Catholic LA parish, 'it's like everybody here is a freedom fighter' |url=https://www.dailynews.com/2021/01/29/at-poet-amanda-gormans-black-catholic-la-parish-its-like-everybody-here-is-a-freedom-fighter/ |access-date=2021-02-01 |work=Los Angeles Daily News |agency=Mercury News, Bay Area News Group |date=2021-01-29}}</ref>。她在拜登就職典禮的隔天登上《[[詹姆斯·柯登深夜秀|詹姆斯·柯登深夜秀]]》時稱柯登是其「有史以來最喜歡的人」<ref>{{Cite news|last=Murphy|first=Chris|date=2021-01-22|title=Amanda Gorman Geeking Out Over James Corden Won Late Night This Week|work=Vulture|publisher=[[New_York_(magazine)|New York]]|url=https://www.vulture.com/2021/01/this-week-in-late-night-amanda-gorman-and-james-corden.html|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127192227/https://www.vulture.com/2021/01/this-week-in-late-night-amanda-gorman-and-james-corden.html|archive-date=2021-01-27}}</ref>。Urban Word NYC的執行董事麥可·切雷爾利（Michael Cirelli）稱她是一位「精力充沛的人」，並打趣表示其「個人簡介每隔兩週便會過期」<ref name="Kocharian" />。在2014年，戈爾曼據報希望成為一位人權倡導者<ref name=":5" />。

